<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>I ran into this testing my code using both Zend_Uri_Http and Zend_Http_Client. Since the client mutates the argument, setting the port to a default port (See ZF-11162), it was hard for me to assert equality between expected URI's and actual URI's in my unit test.</p>

<p>Imho, it would be nicer if Zend_Uri_Http ignores the port number in the constructed string URL if it is the default for the current scheme. See the provided patch and unit test.</p>

<p>Maybe there should be an option 'ignoreDefaultPorts' or an argument for the getUri() method, I'm not sure.</p>

